news.title: Property registration in Pune dips 17% in January 2026: Knight Frank
news.para: Pune saw 14,527 property registrations in January 2026, generating ₹609 crore. Registrations dropped 17% year-on-year, but revenue fell slower at 5%. This indicates a shift towards higher-value property deals. The market showed a rebound from December 2025. Homes priced up to ₹1 crore still dominated, but their share moderated.

news.title: GCCs may account for up to 50% of India’s office demand: Report
news.para: Global Capability Centres are set to fuel India's office space market. These centres will account for half of the demand in major cities. Annual leasing by GCCs is predicted to reach 35 to 40 million square feet. This growth signifies a significant shift in office space absorption.

news.title: Average home sizes rise 17% in two years across top seven cities
news.para: Indian cities are seeing bigger homes. Average apartment sizes grew 17% in two years. This means more demand for larger homes and premium housing. NCR saw a 30% jump in size. Hyderabad has the largest homes. This trend started after the pandemic, with overall sizes increasing significantly.

news.title: Over 350 government land lease violations detected across district; Pune city, Haveli taluka top the chart
news.para: Pune city and Haveli taluka have recorded the most violations concerning government land leased long-term. The district administration has issued notices to institutions found to be in breach. These violations include non-renewal of leases, misuse of land, unauthorized constructions, and failure to utilize land as per agreements.

news.title: Central Park to invest ₹1,200 crore to develop residential project in Gurugram
news.para: Central Park Estates is investing ₹1,200 crore in Gurugram's Belanova residential project. This development aims for a revenue of ₹2,500 to ₹3,000 crore. The project features 124 residences, each priced around ₹25 crore. Sales are projected to reach ₹500 crore in FY26 and ₹1,000 crore in FY27.

news.title: Yamuna expressway authority proposes 500 acres each for Japan City, Singapore City
news.para: YEIDA has proposed developing Japan City and Singapore City along the Yamuna Expressway. Land has been identified in Greater Noida's Sector 5A and Sector 7 for these integrated industrial townships. The proposal follows Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath's planned visits to Japan and Singapore. Around 500 acres are earmarked for each city, focusing on industrial use.

news.title: NGT extends Goa sand mining ban till April 23
news.para: Goa's sand mining ban continues as the National Green Tribunal extended interim relief until April 23. This follows a challenge to environmental clearances granted by state authorities. The Goa Coastal Zone Management Authority apologized for a delay in filing its response, which the tribunal accepted. The case centers on alleged violations of Supreme Court guidelines and environmental notifications.

news.title: Isprava acquires two-acre land in South Goa for luxury residential development
news.para: The Mumbai-based developer with early backings from the Dabur’s Burman, Nadir Godrej and Anand Piramal family offices, is planning to build a limited inventory of residences on the plot, with the land parcel acquired through its investment vehicles.

news.title: Davanagere district distributes land title deeds to 12,000 people
news.para: Davanagere district has designated 298 residential areas as revenue villages, distributing title deeds to 12,000 individuals. The district ranks second in deed issuance. Preparations for a digital census, including self-verification, are underway from April 16 to May 15. Strict action is warned against unauthorized flex banners and water lifting from the Bhadra canal.

news.title: Haryana RERA orders compensation to buyers for delay in flat handover in Gurugram
news.para: Haryana RERA has ordered developers Microtek Infrastructures and Deepanshu Projects to pay Rs 41 lakh in compensation to buyers for an eight-year delay in apartment possession. The order includes compensation for loss of appreciation, mental inconvenience, and litigation costs, with interest to be paid until full settlement.

news.title: Nashik: NMC mandates 50:50 use of premium FSI & TDR to boost demand, speed up land acquisition
news.para: Nashik's civic body mandates developers use premium Floor Space Index (FSI) and Transfer of Development Rights (TDR) equally. This aims to revive TDR demand, ensure fair landowner compensation, and facilitate acquiring land for public amenities. The move is expected to reduce the municipal corporation's financial burden and speed up development plan projects.

news.title: Lucknow: Over 5,000 property owners may face sealing, demolition
news.para: Lucknow Development Authority is set to take action against over 5,000 property owners. A survey revealed land-use violations along 24-meter wide roads. Residential properties were found to be used for commercial activities without approval. Notices will be issued soon. Owners must regularize their buildings or stop commercial use. Failure to comply will result in sealing or demolition.

news.title: Real estate tribunal stays MahaRERA chairperson’s order
news.para: The Maharashtra Real Estate Appellate Tribunal has put a hold on a MahaRERA chairperson's order concerning a flat buyer's complaint. The tribunal also called for an investigation into the issuance of two different versions of the same order. This action follows an appeal against the chairperson's decision to set aside previous orders.

news.title: Gurugram: ED attaches ₹82 crore worth of properties in fraud related to 'Ansal Hub-83' project
news.para: The project is spread over a land area of 19 Kanal 15 Marla (approximately 2.47 acres) and consists of 147 commercial shops, 137 office spaces and two restaurant units, ED said on Thursday.

news.title: Rajasthan HC gives housing board three weeks to clear illegal Sanganer colonies
news.para: Rajasthan High Court has given the Rajasthan Housing Board three weeks to remove 87 illegal colonies in Sanganer. The court warned the housing board commissioner must appear if the order is not followed. This follows a petition highlighting the state government's attempt to regularize colonies on land acquired by the housing board.

news.title: HMT land bank may be monetised as AI clusters
news.para: India is preparing a plan to use land owned by HMT Ltd for artificial intelligence clusters. HMT has a large land bank across several states. Investment plans of around ₹10,000 crore are being drawn up for these AI clusters. The government is considering a report on HMT's revival. This initiative aims to clear worker and statutory dues.

news.title: Take action to fix tech issues in offices: CREDAI to Karnataka government
news.para: CREDAI has urged the state government to address technical problems plaguing government offices. These issues are hindering the issuance of e-khatas, causing delays for developers and property owners. CREDAI also called for the removal of the life certificate requirement for GPA registrations. This rule has become a burden for senior citizens and non-residents.

news.title: Pune civic body's GB rejects property tax hike proposal, PCMC likely to maintain status quo
news.para: Pune civic body's general body unanimously dismissed a 5% property tax hike proposal, urging the administration to improve tax recovery and widen the tax net instead. Pimpri Chinchwad residents are also likely to be spared an increase due to the absence of a standing committee, delaying the proposal's submission.

news.title: Land acquisition completed for Google data centre project in Visakhapatnam
news.para: Visakhapatnam district administration has acquired 308 acres in Tarluwada for Google's proposed data centre, a key component of a $15 billion AI hub investment. The project, involving partners like Adani Infra and Bharti Airtel subsidiaries, aims to transform Visakhapatnam into a technology hub, with land acquisition now complete after offering substantial compensation and benefits to assignees.

news.title: Ranchi smart city project gains momentum with land mutation almost resolved
news.para: Ranchi's decade-old Smart City project is finally accelerating as the crucial land mutation issue nears resolution. With over 450 acres mutated and plots allocated, infrastructure is in place.  The ambitious project, aiming for 15,000 homes and advanced amenities, is now poised for significant development, with plans for future phases underway.
